* Then in your `Application` there is `Process process = context.getBean(Process.class);` which makes no sense because `Process` is not a bean class but an annotation. You took my code from the [other answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/57899444/1082681), changed many things and then nothing fit together anymore. Now your application looks like this:

