You should use *fat arrow* to retain the scope so `this` remains pointed to the controller
```js
Rails.ajax({
  url: url,
  type: &#39;GET&#39;,
  success: (data) =&gt; {
    // now this retains to the controller
  }
})
```

By the way you can pass the parameter as follows
```js
const url = &#39;/budget_code_items/budget&#39;
Rails.ajax({
  url: url,
  type: &#39;GET&#39;,
  data: &#39;budget_code_id=&#39; + this.budgetCodeTarget.value,
  success: (data) =&gt; {
  }
})
```

See the more detailed [example][1] for additional controller code structuring.


  [1]: https://gorails.com/forum/populate-dropdowns-based-on-selection-with-stimulus-js#forum_post_14073

